Head of Key Account Management Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of rapidly growing multinational consumer goods company. Our respected client is seeking a sales professional with at least five years’ experience with a respectable consumer goods company for the job of Head of Key Account Management, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia Key job responsibilities will include: Provides guidance to Key Account channel and aligns their targets based on country’s prioritiesCoordinates implementation of strategic priorities in CSI/MNC together with global/regional CSI/MNCFacilitates the development of local Strategic Customers to support budget achievementResponsible for CSI/MNC/SC budget achievement in the countryPlans and manages portfolio of accountsSupports local Key Account Teams (through account planning, joined visits to Top customers) and acts as coach for the Key Account TeamSupports and facilitates  Sales skills/process training relevant to the Key Account channelActively participates in expert community and fosters collaboration Requirements: Bachelor’s degree (minimum) in any major5 years’ experience (minimum) in sales in forwarding industry with three years at the managerial levelGood understanding of sectors issue in the forwarding industryWell-developed management skills and collaborative leadership styleAbility to identify customer needs by gathering information and building long-term relationshipsGood communication and presentation skillsConceptual thinking and analytical skillsComputer-literate (Ms. Office is a must, exposure to CRM platform is preferable)Fluent in English verbal/written communication All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to consumer@monroeconsulting.com
